statements: SELECT * FROM RiskProfiles;
SELECT applicant_name, age, gender FROM RiskProfiles WHERE age > 30;
SELECT id, applicant_name, risk_score FROM RiskProfiles WHERE gender = 'Male';
SELECT * FROM RiskProfiles WHERE occupation = 'Engineer' ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT id, applicant_name, policy_type FROM RiskProfiles WHERE risk_score > 4.5;
SELECT id, applicant_name, age, risk_score FROM RiskProfiles WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY risk_score DESC;
SELECT * FROM RiskProfiles WHERE gender = 'Male' ORDER BY age ASC;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_profiles, AVG(risk_score) AS average_risk_score FROM RiskProfiles WHERE occupation = 'Engineer';
SELECT applicant_name, occupation, policy_type FROM RiskProfiles WHERE policy_type LIKE '%Life%' AND risk_score > 50;
SELECT MAX(risk_score) AS highest_risk_score FROM RiskProfiles WHERE age < 50;
SELECT * FROM risk_profiles;

SELECT applicant_id, historical_risk_score, date_of_record FROM historical_data WHERE applicant_id = 100;

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM risk_profiles;
SELECT applicant_id, risk_score FROM risk_profiles WHERE risk_score > 0.5 ORDER BY risk_score DESC;
SELECT * FROM risk_profiles JOIN historical_data ON risk_profiles.applicant_id = historical_data.applicant_id WHERE historical_risk_score < 0.3 ORDER BY date_of_record;
SELECT applicant_id, MAX(risk_score) AS max_risk_score FROM risk_profiles GROUP BY applicant_id HAVING MAX(risk_score) > 0.8;
SELECT applicant_id, AVG(risk_score) AS avg_risk_score FROM risk_profiles GROUP BY applicant_id HAVING AVG(risk_score) < 0.6;
SELECT applicant_id, COUNT(*) AS record_count FROM historical_data WHERE date_of_record BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31' GROUP BY applicant_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 2 ORDER BY record_count DESC;

SELECT insurance_applicants.name, historical_data.gender, insurance_quotes.quote_amount FROM insurance_applicants INNER JOIN historical_data ON insurance_applicants.applicant_id = historical_data.applicant_id INNER JOIN insurance_quotes ON insurance_applicants.applicant_id = insurance_quotes.applicant_id WHERE historical_data.age > 30;
